<subSubSection id="22A66546FFA9FFE5FF11FEEC49B3FEFE" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="6A0336CDFFA9FFE5FF11FEEC49B3FEFE" blockId="49.[151,1436,289,818]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="58C8EADFFFA9FFE5FF11FEEC4A15FE9A" bold="true" box="[151,278,289,314]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Etymology</emphasis>
. The genus name is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis id="58C8EADFFFA9FFE5FD7BFEEF483EFE99" box="[765,829,290,313]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">arena</emphasis>
= sand, and refers to the small size of the 
<typeStatus id="B507886FFFA9FFE5FA92FEEF4E47FE9A" box="[1300,1348,290,314]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">type</typeStatus>
species comparable to a grain of sand; gender feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="22A66546FFA9FFE5FF41FEA448D7FC92" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="6A0336CDFFA9FFE5FF41FEA44F88FE22" blockId="49.[151,1436,289,818]" box="[199,1163,361,386]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="58C8EADFFFA9FFE5FF41FEA44ACFFE22" bold="true" box="[199,460,361,386]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Diagnosis/Description</emphasis>
. See diagnosis and description of single known species below.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6A0336CDFFA9FFE5FF41FE4048D7FC92" blockId="49.[151,1436,289,818]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="58C8EADFFFA9FFE5FF41FE404A09FE06" bold="true" box="[199,266,397,422]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Notes</emphasis>
. The recent molecular phylogeny of 
<taxonomicName id="ADBC4D4EFFA9FFE5FD2DFE4048FFFE06" authority="(Eberle et al. 2018)" authorityName="Eberle" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Eberle" baseAuthorityYear="2018" box="[683,1020,397,422]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Pholcidae (
<bibRefCitation id="0E2D4B3CFFA9FFE5FCAEFE4048F7FE06" author="Eberle, J. &amp; Dimitrov, D. &amp; Valdez-Mondragon, A. &amp; Huber, B. A." box="[808,1012,397,422]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="141" refId="ref37668" refString="Eberle, J., Dimitrov, D., Valdez-Mondragon, A. &amp; Huber, B. A. (2018) Microhabitat change drives diversification in pholcid spiders. BMC Evolutionary Biology, 18, 141. https: // doi. org / 10.1186 / s 12862 - 018 - 1244 - 8" type="journal article" year="2018">
Eberle 
<emphasis id="58C8EADFFFA9FFE5FCFCFE4348B0FE06" box="[890,947,397,422]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
placed this genus/species as sister to an undescribed species from 
<collectingCountry id="12AB765DFFA9FFE5FE6EFE7C4954FE6A" box="[488,599,433,458]" name="Argentina" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(“Gen.n. MACN270”), and both among ‘basal’ 
<taxonomicName id="ADBC4D4EFFA9FFE5FB0DFE7C4E20FE6A" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1893" box="[1163,1315,433,458]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Modisiminae">Modisiminae</taxonomicName>
. However, relationships among ‘basal’ 
<taxonomicName id="ADBC4D4EFFA9FFE5FE55FE184964FE4E" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1893" box="[467,615,469,494]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Modisiminae">Modisiminae</taxonomicName>
were poorly resolved, so the closest relatives of 
<taxonomicName id="ADBC4D4EFFA9FFE5FB0EFE1B4FD8FE4D" authority="Huber &amp; Carvalho, 2019" authorityName="Huber &amp; Carvalho" authorityYear="2019" box="[1160,1243,470,493]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Arenita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="49" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis id="58C8EADFFFA9FFE5FB0EFE1B4FD8FE4D" box="[1160,1243,470,493]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Arenita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(beyond “Gen.n. MACN270”) remain unknown. The new species described below and “Gen.n. MACN270” are unusual among 
<taxonomicName id="ADBC4D4EFFA9FFE5FF11FDD04A28FD96" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1893" box="[151,299,541,566]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Modisiminae">Modisiminae</taxonomicName>
in lacking an apophysis on the male palpal coxa, in having the PME and ALE very close together, in lacking a thoracic furrow; and in having the plesiomorphic set of ALS spigots (i.e. with 7–8 spigots on each ALS, see below; this character was not studied in “Gen.n. MACN270”). The latter character is only shared by the mysterious genus 
<taxonomicName id="ADBC4D4EFFA9FFE5FEE6FD444950FD02" authority="Simon, 1893" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1893" box="[352,595,649,674]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Priscula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="58C8EADFFFA9FFE5FEE6FD444ABCFD02" box="[352,447,649,674]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Priscula</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="0E2D4B3CFFA9FFE5FE42FD444950FD02" author="Simon, E." box="[452,595,649,674]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="256 - 488" refId="ref39605" refString="Simon, E. (1893) Histoire Naturelle des Araignees. 1 (2). 2 nd edition. Roret, Paris, 233 pp. [pp. 256 - 488]" type="book chapter" year="1893">Simon, 1893</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="0E2D4B3CFFA9FFE5FDE7FD4449E8FD02" author="Huber, B. A." box="[609,747,649,674]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="1 - 348" refId="ref37855" refString="Huber, B. A. (2000) New World pholcid spiders (Araneae: Pholcidae): a revision at generic level. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 254, 1 - 348. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 (2000) 254 &lt;0001: nwpsap&gt; 2.0. co; 2" type="journal article" year="2000">Huber 2000</bibRefCitation>
), whose position within 
<taxonomicName id="ADBC4D4EFFA9FFE5FC7CFD444F8DFD02" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1893" box="[1018,1166,649,674]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Modisiminae">Modisiminae</taxonomicName>
is far from clear (Huber 
<emphasis id="58C8EADFFFA9FFE5FF11FD634BD2FD66" box="[151,209,685,710]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">et al.</emphasis>
2018). At the same time, 
<taxonomicName id="ADBC4D4EFFA9FFE5FE7AFD6349D1FD66" authorityName="Huber &amp; Carvalho" authorityYear="2019" box="[508,722,685,710]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Arenita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fazendinha">
<emphasis id="58C8EADFFFA9FFE5FE7AFD6349D1FD66" box="[508,722,685,710]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Arenita fazendinha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has several highly distinctive characters (see diagnosis below) that are not present in “Gen.n. MACN270”, justifying the creation of a new monotypic genus. The undescribed species “Gen.n. MACN270” will be treated in a separate paper together with further undescribed congeneric species present in Argentinean collections (M.A. Izquierdo, unpubl. data).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
